PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - In this paper the author examines the concept of power and power linkages. He notes that pervious studies have usually focused on the existence of power of specific levels; however, he aims to show that relationships exist between power on the societal, organizational and individuals levels. He contends that power on the organizational level mirrors power on the societal level and because of this organizational power reinforces the attitudes and behavior that society promotes. He discusses several models of power, noting that because the study of power is the study of people an interdisciplinary approach will benefit researchers.
AB  - In this paper the author examines the concept of power and power linkages. He notes that pervious studies have usually focused on the existence of power of specific levels; however, he aims to show that relationships exist between power on the societal, organizational and individuals levels. He contends that power on the organizational level mirrors power on the societal level and because of this organizational power reinforces the attitudes and behavior that society promotes. He discusses several models of power, noting that because the study of power is the study of people an interdisciplinary approach will benefit researchers.
